    "actor_description": "Something in me eases-small, but unmistakable. The future isn't only a block of grey; it has a seam in it. I catch myself running a scenario that doesn't end in damage control, and my body responds before I can argue it down: a longer breath, shoulders dropping a fraction, the faint urge to lean forward instead of brace. I don't trust it enough to celebrate. I just let it exist. A thin thread of \"this might work\" pulls tight and holds.",
    "description_text": "{actor} stops looking past everything and starts looking at something. Their posture tips forward by a degree-chin up, shoulders un-hunched-as if a better outcome just became thinkable. The tightness in their face unknots; their gaze steadies, less defensive, and for a moment they seem to occupy the room instead of enduring it.",
    "alternate_descriptions": {
